> Is the only problem here only the mismatched storage driver? If so why not just create /etc/containers/storage.conf with overlayfs as driver.

That would solve the issue in CI afaics, but issue mentioned here https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/13808#issuecomment-1568815229 will persists for users who used created setup without `storage.conf` just like its breaking in the CI now.

@Luap99 but yes I agree that we should unblock CI if everybody is cool with it.

>What I do see however is https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/5478
>
>if platform.OS == "" {
>	platform.OS = runtime.GOOS
>}

Nice catch, @Luap99 . Removing those three lines (and the `import runtime`) appears to fix the problem.
